title: Telstra outage across Australia after Sydney fire - ABC News (Australian Broadcasting Corporation)
text:
Telstra outage across Australia after Sydney fire Posted February 02, 2017 14:43:17 
Telstra customers are reporting a mobile network outage across the country, with the company saying a fire at their Chatswood exchange in Sydney is impacting services. 
Customers tweeted complaints from around Australia, including Sydney, Melbourne, rural NSW and Western Australia. 
Telstra responded via Twitter, saying a fire at the Chatswood exchange seemed to be affecting services. 
More to come.
